text=(:title Hunter Character Creation:)%0a[[#htop]]%0a[[GameRef.HunterCharacterCreation?action=edit|Click here to Edit]]%0a(:table border=0 style=float width=40%25 align=right  cellspacing=0 :)%0a(:cellnr align=center:)%0a(:cellnr:)%0a(:cellnr bgcolor=#305d52 align=center:)%0a'''Contents'''%0a(:cellnr:) %0a*[[#Creation| Character Creation]]%0a*[[#Restricted| Book List]]%0a*[[#ixp| Incentive XP]]%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a[[#Creation]]%0a[++'''Character Creation'''++]%0a%0a'''General Guidelines'''%0a%0a* No Attributes at 1. Hunters with such a distinct weakness do not last long, even in San Diego.\\%0a* Characters can be members of both a Compact and a Conspiracy provided that they purchase the required Status.\\%0a* Status in a Compact or Conspiracy does not indicate that a character has any Status that they have not purchased or otherwise added to their sheet. For example: Status (Ashwood Abbey) 3 does not allow a character to influence High Society unless he or she buys Status (High Society).%0a%0a'''Compacts'''%0a%0a* Ashwood Abbey, Long Night, Loyalists of Thule, Network Zero, Null Mysteriis, and The Union are available Compacts.\\%0a* Compact Status is subject to the same restrictions as any other Status.\\%0a* Compact Endowments from the ''Compacts and Conspiracies'' book are permitted for use. A Compact Endowment rated at 4 is one Restricted Slot; one rated at 5 is two Restricted Slots. Compact Status is required for any level of Compact Endowment.\\%0a* Characters with Compact Status 1 or more can opt to identify with one of the Factions of that group. If they do, they get the free Specialty associated with that group as outlined in Compacts and Conspiracies. Please place your Faction in the "Notes" section of your character sheet if applicable.\\%0a-Characters may join the [[HunterSanDiegoCompact|San Diego]] Compact and still have a 'from the book' Compact.\\%0a%0a'''Conspiracies'''%0a%0a* Aegis Kai Doru, Ascending Ones, Cheiron Group, Lucifuge, Malleus Maleficarum, and Task Force: VALKYRIE are available Conspiracies.\\%0a* Conspiracy Status 1 is one Restricted Slot. Conspiracy Status 2+ is banned.\\%0a* Conspiracy Endowments require a Restricted Slot in addition to the Status required to purchase them. Allocating a Restricted Slot in this way allows the player to purchase 3 dots worth of Advanced Armory, Elixir, Relic, or Thaumatechnology, or 2 dots worth of Benedictions or Castigation. \\%0a* Additional Benediction Rituals cannot be purchased during character creation. You cannot allocate multiple restricted slots to Endowments in order to purchase beyond the stated limit at character creation.\\%0a* Members of the Ascending Ones can use General XP and Incentive XP to purchase additional doses of the Elixirs they choose at creation within reason. They cannot use it to purchase different Elixirs.%0a* Conspiracy factions will not convey any mechanical benefit.\\%0a* Endowments from Restricted sources may or may not be approved. If you are interested in starting with a particular Endowment that isn't from the core, it is suggested that you discuss it prior to sanctioning with the STs.%0a%0a'''Specific Concerns'''%0a%0a%0a%0a[--%25color=#305d52%25[[#htop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a[[#Restricted]]%0a[++'''Book List'''++]%0a%0a''Open''\\%0aHunter: the Vigil (core rulebook)%0a%0a''Restricted''\\%0aCompacts and Conspiracies\\%0aNight Stalkers\\%0aSpirit Slayers\\%0aWitch Finders%0a%0a''ST-Only''\\%0aBlock by Bloody Block\\%0aHorror Recognition Guide\\%0aSlasher%0a%0a[--%25color=#305d52%25[[#htop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a[[#ixp]]%0a[++'''Incentive XP'''++]\\%0a''Players may have a maximum of +5 Venue iXP and +5 WoD iXP at creation ''%0a%0a%0a[--%25color=#305d52%25[[#htop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a%0a(:include CityBook.HunterNavigationBar:)
